The paper deals with image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The method proposed in the paper involves compression of textures and boundaries, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Gaussian distribution for modeling textures is also related to statistical learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
